f=Engineering/mia/custom/frontend-performance/assets/stack-notes-react-next-2026-07.md · h1:Stack Notes React/Next.js Patterns (dated 2026-07)=**Applies business's stack-profile names React/Next.js.** Method authority: mia's custom skills (`frontend-performance` perf, `ui-accessibility-standards` a11y conflicts resolve there). Source: affaan-m/everything-claude-code `frontend-patterns`, adopted 2026-07-10, condensed. · h2:Component patterns=**Composition over inheritance:** small typed components assembled (`Card` `CardHeader` `CardBody`), never class hierarchies., **Compound components:** shared state context (`Tabs`/`Tab` `TabsContext`); throw clear error child used outside provider., **Render props** reusable data-loading wrappers hooks don't fit. · h2:Hooks=Custom hooks any reused logic: `useToggle`, `useDebounce(value, delay)`., Data-fetching hook trap (source's hard-won note): keep `fetcher`/`options` **refs** `refetch` stays referentially stable inline function/object props otherwise recreate callback render infinite fetch loop. · h2:State=Context reducer feature-level state (typed action unions); hook accessor throws outside provider., Functional updates always (`setX(prev ...)`)., Heavier stores (Zustand etc.) stack-profile. · h2:Performance (feeds frontend-performance's measured-wins rule)=`useMemo` expensive computes **copy before sort** (`[...markets].sort(...)`; sort mutates)., `useCallback` functions passed children; `React.memo` pure list items., Code-split heavy components (`lazy` `Suspense` skeleton fallbacks)., Virtualize long lists (@tanstack/react-virtual: estimated row height overscan)., still subject frontend-performance's rule: measure first, keep measured wins. · h2:Forms=Controlled inputs typed `FormData`/`FormErrors` validate before submit, per-field error display schema validation (Zod) shared API edge possible. · h2:Error boundaries=Class-based `ErrorBoundary` (`getDerivedStateFromError` `componentDidCatch`) wrapping app/feature roots retry fallback. · h2:Accessibility (cross-ref: ui-accessibility-standards owns checklist)=Keyboard navigation custom widgets (Arrow/Enter/Escape handling, `role`/`aria-expanded`/`aria-haspopup`) modal focus management (save previous focus, focus dialog open, restore close, `aria-modal`, Escape closes). · h2:Animation=AnimatePresence/motion patterns (list enter/exit, modal overlay+content) respect reduced-motion ui-accessibility-standards.